{"id":1197,"date":"2021-07-21T14:55:36","date_gmt":"2021-07-21T14:55:36","guid":{"rendered":"https:\/\/operativereview.com\/?page_id=1197"},"modified":"2022-04-12T20:57:28","modified_gmt":"2022-04-12T20:57:28","slug":"rpc-ipaa","status":"publish","type":"page","link":"https:\/\/operativereview.com\/rpc-ipaa\/","title":{"rendered":"RPC-IPAA"},"content":{"rendered":"\t\t<div data-elementor-type=\"wp-page\" data-elementor-id=\"1197\" class=\"elementor elementor-1197\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-inner\">\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-section-wrap\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<section class=\"elementor-section elementor-top-section elementor-element elementor-element-237806f elementor-section-stretched elementor-section-boxed elementor-section-height-default elementor-section-height-default\" data-id=\"237806f\" data-element_type=\"section\" data-settings=\"{&quot;stretch_section&quot;:&quot;section-stretched&quot;}\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-container elementor-column-gap-default\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-row\">\n\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-column elementor-col-100 elementor-top-column elementor-element elementor-element-24d83c2\" data-id=\"24d83c2\" data-element_type=\"column\">\n\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-column-wrap elementor-element-populated\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-widget-wrap\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-element elementor-element-8178bf5 elementor-widget elementor-widget-heading\" data-id=\"8178bf5\" data-element_type=\"widget\" data-widget_type=\"heading.default\">\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-widget-container\">\n\t\t\t<h1 class=\"elementor-heading-title elementor-size-default\">Anorectal: Restorative Proctocolectomy with Ileal Pouch-Anal Anastomosis (RPC-IPAA)<\/h1>\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t<\/section>\n\t\t\t\t<section class=\"elementor-section elementor-top-section elementor-element elementor-element-3fb9b3c elementor-section-stretched elementor-section-boxed elementor-section-height-default elementor-section-height-default\" data-id=\"3fb9b3c\" data-element_type=\"section\" data-settings=\"{&quot;stretch_section&quot;:&quot;section-stretched&quot;}\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-container elementor-column-gap-default\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-row\">\n\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-column elementor-col-100 elementor-top-column elementor-element elementor-element-cc88e83\" data-id=\"cc88e83\" data-element_type=\"column\">\n\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-column-wrap elementor-element-populated\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-widget-wrap\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-element elementor-element-8fa06ee elementor-widget elementor-widget-heading\" data-id=\"8fa06ee\" data-element_type=\"widget\" data-widget_type=\"heading.default\">\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-widget-container\">\n\t\t\t<h2 class=\"elementor-heading-title elementor-size-default\">Restorative Proctocolectomy with Ileal Pouch Anal Anastomosis (RPC-IPAA)<\/h2>\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t<\/section>\n\t\t\t\t<section class=\"elementor-section elementor-top-section elementor-element elementor-element-6d3676e elementor-section-stretched elementor-section-boxed elementor-section-height-default elementor-section-height-default\" data-id=\"6d3676e\" data-element_type=\"section\" data-settings=\"{&quot;stretch_section&quot;:&quot;section-stretched&quot;}\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-container elementor-column-gap-default\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-row\">\n\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-column elementor-col-50 elementor-top-column elementor-element elementor-element-caa7ac5\" data-id=\"caa7ac5\" data-element_type=\"column\">\n\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-column-wrap elementor-element-populated\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-widget-wrap\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-element elementor-element-a9aafa1 elementor-widget elementor-widget-text-editor\" data-id=\"a9aafa1\" data-element_type=\"widget\" data-widget_type=\"text-editor.default\">\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-widget-container\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-text-editor elementor-clearfix\">\n\t\t\t\t<p><strong>Definitions<\/strong><\/p><ul><li><em>Restorative Proctocolectomy<\/em> \u2013 Complete Colon &amp; Rectum Resection Sparing the Anus for Reconstruction<\/li><li><em>Ileal Pouch-Anal Anastomosis<\/em> \u2013 Ileum Loop Folded onto Itself Creating a Pouch for Anastomosis<ul><li>Pouch Allows Reservoir to Decrease Bowel Movement Frequency<\/li><\/ul><\/li><li>Often Done as a Two-Stage Procedure with Initial Diverting Loop Ileostomy<\/li><\/ul><p><strong>Possible Candidates<\/strong><\/p><ul><li>Inflammatory Bowel Disease without Rectal Involvement Refractory to Medical Management<ul><li>Generally Used in Ulcerative Colitis but <strong>Not for Crohn\u2019s Disease<\/strong><\/li><\/ul><\/li><li>Familial Adenomatous Polyposis (FAP)<\/li><li>Severe Colonic Inertia Refractory to Medical Therapy (Ileorectal Anastomosis Preferred)<\/li><\/ul><p><strong>Contraindications<\/strong><\/p><ul><li>Absolute:<ul><li>Severe Fecal Incontinence<\/li><li>Low Rectal CA Involving Sphincters<\/li><li>Perianal Crohn\u2019s Disease<\/li><\/ul><\/li><li>Relative:<ul><li>Morbid Obesity<\/li><li>Low Rectal CA with Neoadjuvant Tx<\/li><li>Non-Perianal Crohn\u2019s Disease<\/li><li>Prior Extensive Small Bowel Resection<\/li><\/ul><\/li><\/ul><p><strong>Ileal Pouch Types<\/strong><\/p><ul><li>J-Pouch (2-Limbs)<ul><li>Preferred Type<\/li><li>Length: <strong>15-20<\/strong> cm<\/li><\/ul><\/li><li>Rare Alternative Types:<ul><li>S-Pouch (3-Limbs)<\/li><li>W-Pouch (4-Limbs)<\/li><\/ul><\/li><\/ul><p><strong>Techniques to Decrease Tension or Ensure Reach<\/strong><\/p><ul><li>Division of Ileum Flush with Cecum<\/li><li>Complete Mobilization of Small Intestine to the Third Portion of Duodenum<\/li><li>Full Adhesiolysis<\/li><li>Transverse-Stepladder Relaxing Incisions Over the Mesentery Under Tension Along SMA Vessels<\/li><\/ul><p><strong>Pouchitis<\/strong><\/p><ul><li>Most Common Long-Term Complication (23-59%)<ul><li>Higher-Risk if Resection Due to Ulcerative Colitis<\/li><\/ul><\/li><li><em>Infectious Pouchitis<\/em><ul><li>Cause: Inflammation of Pouch from Infection<ul><li>Postoperative Microbiome of Pouch Transitions from Ileum-Like to Colon-Like<\/li><li>No Specific Pathogens Have Been Consistently Implicated<\/li><\/ul><\/li><li>Sx: Diarrhea, Bloody Stools, Pain &amp; Fever<\/li><li>Tx: Oral ABX (<strong>Ciprofloxacin #1<\/strong>, Metronidazole or Tinidazole)<ul><li>Consider Biopsy to <strong>Rule Out Chron\u2019s Disease<\/strong><\/li><\/ul><\/li><\/ul><\/li><li><em>Diversion\/Disuse Pouchitis<\/em><ul><li><a href=\"http:\/\/operativereview.com\/diversion-colitis\/\">*See Large Intestine: Diversion Colitis<\/a><\/li><li>Cause: Inflammation of Pouch from Diversion by Loop Ileostomy Due to Deficiency of SCFA\u2019s<\/li><li>Preferred Tx: Surgical Reanastomosis<\/li><li>If Unable to Reanastomose: <strong>SCFA Enema<\/strong><ul><li>Consider Topical Anti-Inflammatory (5-ASA\/Steroids)<\/li><\/ul><\/li><\/ul><\/li><\/ul>\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-column elementor-col-50 elementor-top-column elementor-element elementor-element-d07ec16\" data-id=\"d07ec16\" data-element_type=\"column\">\n\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-column-wrap elementor-element-populated\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-widget-wrap\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-element elementor-element-c3d0a37 elementor-widget elementor-widget-text-editor\" data-id=\"c3d0a37\" data-element_type=\"widget\" data-widget_type=\"text-editor.default\">\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-widget-container\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t